## Tasks and Steps

1.  Download and open the empty starter file.
2.  An important Excel feature is Conditional Formatting. [Mac](https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/office/use-conditional-formatting-to-highlight-information-in-excel-fed60dfa-1d3f-4e13-9ecb-f1951ff89d7f) [Win](https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/office/use-conditional-formatting-to-highlight-information-in-excel-fed60dfa-1d3f-4e13-9ecb-f1951ff89d7f) It is a powerful functionality to highlight relevant information. For example, in the Calculations worksheet:

-   Highlight in red all the chains that have more than 100 units (column B).
-   Highlight in green all the chains that have more than 100,000,000 dollars in gross sales (column C).
-   Highlight in yellow all the dates that are a duplicate (column F). A duplicate is a value that appears more than once in the column.

3.  After you apply the above steps you realize that too much conditional formatting is hampering your design. You basically, end up not highlighting anything when everything is highlighted. You can resolve this problem:

-   Modify the conditional formatting in column B. Use 500 the threshold (i.e., the number of units above which you apply the formatting).
-   Modify the conditional formatting of column C. Update the gross sales amount to 500,000,000 dollars. What did you notice?
-   Clear the conditional formatting for the dates (column F). They are all the same.

4.  On the Calculations worksheet do the following:

-   Format column D using blue Data Bars (select the Solid Fill option).
-   Format column E using a Top/bottom rule that highlights only the values above the average (use green as the color). [Mac](https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/office/use-conditional-formatting-to-highlight-information-in-excel-fed60dfa-1d3f-4e13-9ecb-f1951ff89d7f) [Win](https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/office/use-conditional-formatting-to-highlight-information-in-excel-fed60dfa-1d3f-4e13-9ecb-f1951ff89d7f)

5.  Use find and replace to change all dates to 01/01/2016. Try to perform this step using the keyboard shortcuts and updating all the dates simultaneously. [Mac](https://support.microsoft.com/en-gb/office/find-or-replace-text-and-numbers-on-a-worksheet-0e304ca5-ecef-4808-b90f-fdb42f892e90#ID0EACAAA=Mac) [Win](https://support.microsoft.com/en-gb/office/find-or-replace-text-and-numbers-on-a-worksheet-0e304ca5-ecef-4808-b90f-fdb42f892e90#ID0EACAAA=Windows)
6.  Save the file and close it.

